Date: 1997-07-09

Title: Note on thermodynamic fermion loop under constant magnetic field

Comments: 8 pages

Journal-ref: J.Math.Phys. 39 (1998) 4540

The one-loop effective potential of a thermodynamic fermion loop underconstant magnetic field is studied. As expected, it can be interpretedliterally as a discretized sum of $(D-2)$-dimensional energy density above theDirac sea. Large/small mass expansions of the potential are also examined.